HEADWORD: lingcod
<hw>lingcod</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The flesh of a
lean-fleshed fish caught off the U.S. Pacific coast.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A food fish (<spn>Ophiodon elongatus</spn>) of
Northern Pacific waters related to greenlings.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Ophiodon elongatus.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

